(450, 1, '2015-03-10 08:20:48', '2015-03-10 08:20:48', '<h3>Privacy Policy</h3>\r\n<h3>\r\n<br>\r\nWhat information do we collect about me?</h3>\r\nLAKEMEAWAYLBJ.COM collects personal identifying information (“PII”) from you only when you voluntarily register / submit such information on our website or subscribe to our email newsletter. PII may include your name, postal address, email address, telephone / mobile phone numbers, and all other information you provide to us. When visiting or registering on our online website, we collect user-specific information on what pages are visited and any volunteered information such as survey information and/or website registrations.\r\nLAKEMEAWAYLBJ.COM may also collect information about your interaction with our website and services including, but not limited to, information from your browser, the website from which you came, the search engine(s) and keywords used to find our website, the pages you visit within our website, your browser add-ons and your browser’s width and height. We may also use technologies, such as cookies, to collect information about the pages you view, the links that you click and other actions you take as they related to our website. Additionally, we may collect certain standard information that your browser sends to every website you visit, such as your IP address, browser type, browser language, access times and referring website addresses. We may use this information collected alone or in combination with other information obtained from other companies to offer you a more consistent and personalized experience in your interactions with our website.\r\n<h3>How do we use information collected?</h3>\r\nAny of the PII and other information collected from you when you visit LAKEMEAWAYLBJ.COM may be used in one of the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To personalize your experience in your interaction with our website</li>\r\n	<li>To improve our website content and overall user experience</li>\r\n	<li>To administer a contest, promotion, survey or other site feature</li>\r\n	<li>To send periodic emails</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>How can I update my information or stop receiving emails from LAKEMEAWAYLBJ.COM?</h3>\r\nIf at any time you would like to unsubscribe from receiving future emails, we include detailed unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of each email communication.\r\n<h3>How do we protect your information?</h3>\r\nLAKEMEAWAYLBJ.COM ensures the security of your data by implementing a variety of security measures such as industry-standard encryption technologies when transferring and receiving consumer data exchanged with our website. We have security measures that protect against the loss, misuse or alteration of information that we collect from you.\r\n<h3>What are “cookies” and do we use them?</h3>\r\n“Cookies” are small files that a website or its service provider transfers to your computer’s hard drive through your web browser (if you allow for it) that enables the websites or service providers systems to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information.\r\nYes, we do use cookies to keep track of advertisements and compile aggregate data about website traffic and interactions so that we can offer better website experiences, services and tools in the future. We may contract with third-party service providers to assist us in better understanding our site visitors. These service providers are not permitted to use the information collected on our behalf except to help us conduct and improve our business.\r\nYou can disable cookies using simple procedures in most Internet browsers that allow you to turn them off. Please remember, however, that cookies may be required to allow you to use certain features of our website.\r\n<h3>Do we disclose any information to outside parties?</h3>\r\nWe do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your PII or other personal information. This does not include, however, trusted third parties who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you, so long as those parties agree to keep this information confidential. We may also release your information when we believe release is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our site policies, or to protect our rights or the rights of others, property, or safety. However, non-personally identifiable visitor information may be provided to other parties for marketing, advertising, or other uses.\r\n<h3>Third party links</h3>\r\nOccasionally, at our discretion, we may include or offer third party products or services on our website. These third party websites have separate and independent privacy policies. We, therefore, have no responsibility or liability for the content and activities of these linked websites. Nonetheless, we seek to protect the integrity of our website and welcome any feedback about these sites.\r\n<h3>California Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance</h3>\r\nBecause we value your privacy we have taken the necessary precautions to be in compliance with the California Online Privacy Protection Act. We, therefore, will not distribute your personal information to outside parties without your consent.\r\n<h3>Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance</h3>\r\nWe are in compliance with the requirements of COPPA (Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act) and we do not collect any information from anyone under 13 years of age. Our website, products and services are all directed to people who are at least 13 years old or older.\r\n<h3>Online Privacy Policy Only</h3>\r\nThis online privacy policy applies only to information collected through our website and not to information collected offline.\r\n<h3>Changes to our Privacy Policy</h3>\r\nLAKEMEAWAYLBJ.COM may need to make changes to this privacy policy from time to time in order to address new issues, evolving technologies, changes on our website, or business practices. Please refer back to this policy regularly.', 'Privacy Policy', '', '