(889, 1, '2015-04-01 09:37:56', '2015-04-01 09:37:56', '<div class="total_link_text">\r\n<div class="extrnl_tab_link">\r\n[sidebar name="The Area Menu Sidebar"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right_text">\r\n[seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>About the Area</h3>\r\nThere is something very special about the Texas Hill Country. From the unforgettable wildflowers to the breathtaking sunsets, this area bears the pride of Texas. Lake LBJ, part of the Highland Lakes chain, is one of the most popular lakes in Texas.\r\n\r\nThe area attracts visitors from all over the world and offers a wide variety of things to do including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Boating</li>\r\n	<li>Kayaking</li>\r\n	<li>Jet Skiing</li>\r\n	<li>Fishing</li>\r\n	<li>Golfing</li>\r\n	<li>Hiking Trails</li>\r\n	<li>Wineries</li>\r\n	<li>Breweries</li>\r\n	<li>Dining</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCome experience the friendly hospitality of the Texas Hill Country!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/TheArea.png" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last]\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'About the Area', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-the-area', '', '', '2015-04-01 10:30:07', '2015-04-01 10:30:07', '', 0, '?page_id=889', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(857, 1, '2015-03-31 11:23:40', '2015-03-31 11:23:40', '[tabs type="vertical"]\r\n[tab title="About the Area"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>About the Area</h3>\r\nThere is something very special about the Texas Hill Country. From the unforgettable wildflowers to the breathtaking sunsets, this area bears the pride of Texas. Lake LBJ, part of the Highland Lakes chain, is one of the most popular lakes in Texas.<br/>\r\nThe area attracts visitors from all over the world and offers a wide variety of things to do including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Boating</li>\r\n	<li>Kayaking</li>\r\n	<li>Jet Skiing</li>\r\n	<li>Fishing</li>\r\n	<li>Golfing</li>\r\n	<li>Hiking Trails</li>\r\n	<li>Wineries</li>\r\n	<li>Breweries</li>\r\n	<li>Dining</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCome experience the friendly hospitality of the Texas Hill Country!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/TheArea.png" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Lake LBJ / Highland Lakes"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Lake LBJ / Highland Lakes</h3>\r\nLake LBJ, named after President Lyndon B. Johnson, is part of the Highland Lakes chain of seven lakes starting in Austin and spanning northwest for more than 85 miles. Originally called Lake Granite Shoals, the reservoir was formed in 1950 by the construction of Granite Shoals Dam by the Lower Colorado River Authority. The lake was renamed to Lake Lyndon B. Johnson (“LBJ”) in 1965 in honor of the former President of the U.S.<br/>\r\nLake LBJ is one of seven fresh water reservoirs that make up the Highland Lakes formed by several dams on the Colorado River. This portion of the river winds southeast from its headwaters near the border of Texas and New Mexico to Matagorda Bay and the Gulf of Mexico. The dams provide flood control and are used to generate hydroelectric power and recreational opportunities.<br/>\r\nLake LBJ is one of the largest constant level lakes in the U.S. and is just over 21 miles long with a maximum width of 10,800 feet. As one of the most popular lakes in Texas, it is perfect for a variety of water activities and an outdoor lifestyle!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/HighlandLakes.GIF" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Map"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Map</h3>\r\n<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27482.33310246459!2d-98.37808235!3d30.569311599999992!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x865b03c890b85f27%3A0x66ddc396f46f2257!2sLake+Lyndon+B+Johnson%2C+Texas%2C+USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1426165477704" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe>[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last][/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Driving Directions"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Driving Directions</h3>\r\nFrom Austin: Approx. 55 miles / 1.10 hour by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on TX-71 W</li>\r\n	<li>Drive approx. 55 miles</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right onto FM 2147 E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFrom Dallas: Approx. 210 miles / 3.75 hours by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on I-35 E S</li>\r\n	<li>Get on US-67 S and take it 86 miles to TX-220 S in Erath County</li>\r\n	<li>Take a slight left onto TX-220 S</li>\r\n	<li>Follow US-281 S for 103 miles to FM 2147 W in Marble Falls</li>\r\n	<li>Continue on FM 2147 W</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFrom San Antonio: Approx. 98 miles / 2 hours by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on I-37 N</li>\r\n	<li>Get on US-281 N and take it 90 miles to TX-71 W</li>\r\n	<li>Get on TX-71 W to FM 2147 E</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right onto FM 2147 E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27482.33310246459!2d-98.37808235!3d30.569311599999992!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x865b03c890b85f27%3A0x66ddc396f46f2257!2sLake+Lyndon+B+Johnson%2C+Texas%2C+USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1426165477704" width="360" height="448" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe>[/five_twelfths_last][/tab][tab title="Local Weather"]\r\n<h3>Local Weather</h3>\r\nBelow is a monthly overview of the weather in the area based on data from Kingsland, Texas.\r\n\r\n[five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Weather.png" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][button url="http://www.weather.com/weather/today/l/30.56,-98.35?lat=30.56&amp;lon=-98.35&amp;locale=en_US&amp;temp=f" size="medium" target="_blanck"]Current Weather[/button][/tab][/tabs]', 'THE AREA', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '489-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 11:23:40', '2015-03-31 11:23:40', '', 489, '489-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(880, 1, '2015-03-31 15:28:45', '2015-03-31 15:28:45', '[tabs type="vertical"]\r\n[tab title="About the Area"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>About the Area</h3>\r\nThere is something very special about the Texas Hill Country. From the unforgettable wildflowers to the breathtaking sunsets, this area bears the pride of Texas. Lake LBJ, part of the Highland Lakes chain, is one of the most popular lakes in Texas.<br/>\r\nThe area attracts visitors from all over the world and offers a wide variety of things to do including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Boating</li>\r\n	<li>Kayaking</li>\r\n	<li>Jet Skiing</li>\r\n	<li>Fishing</li>\r\n	<li>Golfing</li>\r\n	<li>Hiking Trails</li>\r\n	<li>Wineries</li>\r\n	<li>Breweries</li>\r\n	<li>Dining</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCome experience the friendly hospitality of the Texas Hill Country!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/TheArea.png" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Lake LBJ / Highland Lakes"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Lake LBJ / Highland Lakes</h3>\r\nLake LBJ, named after President Lyndon B. Johnson, is part of the Highland Lakes chain of seven lakes starting in Austin and spanning northwest for more than 85 miles. Originally called Lake Granite Shoals, the reservoir was formed in 1950 by the construction of Granite Shoals Dam by the Lower Colorado River Authority. The lake was renamed to Lake Lyndon B. Johnson (“LBJ”) in 1965 in honor of the former President of the U.S.<br/>\r\nLake LBJ is one of seven fresh water reservoirs that make up the Highland Lakes formed by several dams on the Colorado River. This portion of the river winds southeast from its headwaters near the border of Texas and New Mexico to Matagorda Bay and the Gulf of Mexico. The dams provide flood control and are used to generate hydroelectric power and recreational opportunities.<br/>\r\nLake LBJ is one of the largest constant level lakes in the U.S. and is just over 21 miles long with a maximum width of 10,800 feet. As one of the most popular lakes in Texas, it is perfect for a variety of water activities and an outdoor lifestyle!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/HighlandLakes.GIF" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Map"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Map</h3>\r\n<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27482.33310246459!2d-98.37808235!3d30.569311599999992!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x865b03c890b85f27%3A0x66ddc396f46f2257!2sLake+Lyndon+B+Johnson%2C+Texas%2C+USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1426165477704" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe>[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last][/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Driving Directions"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Driving Directions</h3>\r\n<b>From Austin:</b> Approx. 55 miles / 1.10 hour by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on TX-71 W</li>\r\n	<li>Drive approx. 55 miles</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right onto FM 2147 E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>From Dallas:</b> Approx. 210 miles / 3.75 hours by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on I-35 E S</li>\r\n	<li>Get on US-67 S and take it 86 miles to TX-220 S in Erath County</li>\r\n	<li>Take a slight left onto TX-220 S</li>\r\n	<li>Follow US-281 S for 103 miles to FM 2147 W in Marble Falls</li>\r\n	<li>Continue on FM 2147 W</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>From San Antonio:</b> Approx. 98 miles / 2 hours by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on I-37 N</li>\r\n	<li>Get on US-281 N and take it 90 miles to TX-71 W</li>\r\n	<li>Get on TX-71 W to FM 2147 E</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right onto FM 2147 E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27482.33310246459!2d-98.37808235!3d30.569311599999992!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x865b03c890b85f27%3A0x66ddc396f46f2257!2sLake+Lyndon+B+Johnson%2C+Texas%2C+USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1426165477704" width="360" height="448"></iframe>[/five_twelfths_last][/tab][tab title=