liability insurance coverage </li>\r\n<li>Provide a well-stocked home for guests including the following:</li>\r\n<ul class="second_circle">\r\n<li>Furnishings</li>\r\n<li>Towels and bath mats (two par level)</li>\r\n<li>Sheets, blankets and pillows (two par level for sheets)</li>\r\n<li>Kitchen supplies – cookware, utensils, glassware, plates, silverware, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Consumables – toilet paper, paper towels, dish soap, light bulbs, batteries, shampoo, bath soap (LMA can assist with stocking of consumables)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Ensure home is equipped with WI-FI and cable TV</li>\r\n<li>Establish direct relationship with vendors, with LMA assistance if required, for repeat services such as lawn care, pest control, HVAC and pool maintenance</li>\r\n<li>Financial requirements:</li>\r\n<ul class="second_circle">\r\n<li>Initial set up of home including furnishings, linens, kitchen supplies, etc.</li>\r\n<li>Listings costs for VRBO.com and HomeAway.com</li>\r\n<li>Direct billed services such as lawn care, pool care, HVAC service plan and pest control</li>\r\n<li>Payment of all utilities, internet and cable costs</li>\r\n<li>Recommended periodic maintenance such as gutter cleaning and window washing (twice per year)</li>\r\n<li>Cleaning services for Owner or Friend use of property – billed on monthly statement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>What does Lake Me Away charge to manage my home?</h3>\r\n\r\nLake Me Away retains a 25% management fee on all rental revenues collected, including but not limited to, rentals completed, rental fees forfeited and pet fees collected. Merchant fees, as incurred by Lake Me Away, will be the Owner’s responsibility and deducted from rental proceeds.\r\n', 'Owner FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '536-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 14:19:33', '2015-03-31 14:19:33', '', 536, '536-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(879, 1, '2015-03-31 14:31:59', '2015-03-31 14:31:59', '<h3>Why should I rent a home on Lake LBJ?</h3>\r\n\r\nLake LBJ is one of the largest, constant level lakes in the United States, at just over 21 miles long with a maximum width of 10,800 feet. Lake LBJ is perfect for water related activities such as boating, waterskiing, jet skiing, and fishing. Lake LBJ, one of the most popular and beautiful lakes in Texas, was named after President Lyndon B. Johnson, and is part of the Highland Lakes chain of six lakes starting in Austin and going northwest for over 85 miles. Lake LBJ starts at Kingsland, where the Colorado and Llano rivers meet and goes to Horseshoe Bay. Come and enjoy the amazing natural scenery in a luxurious atmosphere where you will be welcomed with open arms!\r\n\r\n<h3>Why should I rent from Lake Me Away?</h3>\r\n\r\nLake Me Away is committed to delivering high quality vacation rental experiences for you, your family and friends. We are experienced business leaders, operators and managers with a depth of knowledge in luxury hospitality, sales and marketing, business and watercraft operation and safety. We believe wonderful vacation experiences in a lovely, lakeside setting creates lifelong memories and we are committed to doing all we can to ensure a relaxing vacation experience. \r\n\r\n<h3>Is the home fully furnished?</h3>\r\n\r\nYes. All homes are fully furnished, both indoors and out. The homes also feature kitchens that are fully stocked with pots, pans, cooking utensils, plates, glassware, silver etc. A “starter” supply of consumables such as trash bags, paper towels, toilet paper, dishwashing soap, laundry detergent etc. is also provided to help make your stay more comfortable.\r\n\r\n<h3>Is there Internet access?</h3>\r\n\r\nYes. All homes feature high-speed WI-FI service. Access codes are located in each home in the House Rules information provided upon your arrival.\r\n\r\n<h3>Is daily housekeeping service provided?</h3>\r\n\r\nNo. Daily housekeeping service is not included but can be arranged for an additional fee.\r\n\r\n<h3>What should I bring and what should I leave at home?</h3>\r\n\r\nWhile homes and kitchens are fully furnished and stocked, you will need to bring personal items such as hairdryers, shampoo, body wash etc. If you plan to enjoy the lake and outdoors, we advise you to bring sunscreen, beach towels, a good book and a hat! Items such as jewelry and other valuables should be left at home. Homes do not have safes and Lake Me Away is not responsible for items lost or stolen.\r\n\r\n<h3>Can I rent a boat or kayak?</h3>\r\n\r\nYes. There are two companies in Kingsland that rent watercrafts and will deliver them to your dock.  Splash Rentals (www.splashrentals.com) and Wave Chasers (www.wavechasersllc.com) both rent watercrafts for your enjoyment. Just Yakin’ Kayak Rental is located in Marble Falls and rents kayaks (www.justyakin.com). Visit the Activities page of our website to learn more.\r\n\r\n<h3>Can I bring my boat or jet skis?</h3>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! Many of the homes have day docks or boat slips for your watercraft; Inquire about the specifics of your property. A public boat ramp is also available in Kingsland.\r\n\r\n<h3>What other activities are available in the area?</h3>\r\n\r\nWhile the Highland Lakes are known for the beautiful water and boating activities, the area also offers opportunities for hiking, shopping, scenic drives, winery and brewery tours, state parks, golf, fishing and much more! Visit the Activities page of our website to learn more.\r\n\r\n<h3>How do we gain access to our rental home?</h3>\r\n\r\nEach home is equipped with either a digital lock or a lock box. Entry instructions and codes will be emailed to you approximately one week prior to your arrival, along with the specific address of the rental home.\r\n\r\n<h3>What are check-in and checkout times?</h3>\r\n\r\nCheck-in time is 4:00 PM Central Time and Checkout time is 11:00 AM Central Time. Requests for an early check-in or late checkout can be made the day prior to your arrival and is subject to a $50 fee.\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the closest airport?</h3>\r\n\r\nAustin Bergstrom International Airport (ABIA) is approximately 70 miles from Kingsland. Rental cars are available at the airport.\r\n\r\n<h3>What if I have to cancel my trip?</h3>\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, cancellations that occur within 30 days of the scheduled arrival date are non-refundable.  Travel insurance is highly recommended. Visit the CSA Travel Protection page of our website to learn more.\r\n\r\n<h3>Are laundry facilities available?</h3>\r\n\r\nYes. Most homes are equipped with a washer and dryer.\r\n\r\n<h3>How do I pay for my visit?</h3>\r\n\r\nWe require a 25% reservation fee at the time of booking, as well as a signed Rental Agreement, Guest Details and Pet Policy (if applicable) in order to confirm a reservation. The remaining balance is charged 30 days prior to arrival and is non-refundable.\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the Smoking Policy?</h3>\r\n\r\nSmoking is not permitted in any of our homes under any circumstances. If we detect that smoking has occurred in one of our homes, a $500 charge will be processed to the credit card on file to deodorize the home.\r\n\r\n<h3>Can I bring my dog?</h3>\r\n\r\nDogs are allowed in some of our rental homes. (Sorry, no cats allowed.) A signed Pet Policy and a paid Pet Fee is required. Visit the Pet Policy page of our website to learn more.\r\n\r\n<h3>What if I break something in the house or if there is damage to the house?</h3>\r\n\r\nA Damage Protection Plan provided by CSA Travel covers most reservations; The plan covers unintentional damage up to $3,000 and is paid for at the time of booking.  \r\n', 'Guest FAQs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '448-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 14:31:59', '2015-03-31 14:31:59', '', 448, '448-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(881, 1, '2015-03-31 15:30:05', '2015-03-31 15:30:05', '[tabs type="vertical"]\r\n[tab title="About the Area"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>About the Area</h3>\r\nThere is something very special about the Texas Hill Country. From the unforgettable wildflowers to the breathtaking sunsets, this area bears the pride of Texas. Lake LBJ, part of the Highland Lakes chain, is one of the most popular lakes in Texas.<br/>\r\nThe area attracts visitors from all over the world and offers a wide variety of things to do including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Boating</li>\r\n	<li>Kayaking</li>\r\n	<li>Jet Skiing</li>\r\n	<li>Fishing</li>\r\n	<li>Golfing</li>\r\n	<li>Hiking Trails</li>\r\n	<li>Wineries</li>\r\n	<li>Breweries</li>\r\n	<li>Dining</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCome experience the friendly hospitality of the Texas Hill Country!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/TheArea.png" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Lake LBJ / Highland Lakes"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Lake LBJ / Highland Lakes</h3>\r\nLake LBJ, named after President Lyndon B. Johnson, is part of the Highland Lakes chain of seven lakes starting in Austin and spanning northwest for more than 85 miles. Originally called Lake Granite Shoals, the reservoir was formed in 1950 by the construction of Granite Shoals Dam by the Lower Colorado River Authority. The lake was renamed to Lake Lyndon B. Johnson (“LBJ”) in 1965 in honor of the former President of the U.S.<br/>\r\nLake LBJ is one of seven fresh water reservoirs that make up the Highland Lakes formed by several dams on the Colorado River. This portion of the river winds southeast from its headwaters near the border of Texas and New Mexico to Matagorda Bay and the Gulf of Mexico. The dams provide flood control and are used to generate hydroelectric power and recreational opportunities.<br/>\r\nLake LBJ is one of the largest constant level lakes in the U.S. and is just over 21 miles long with a maximum width of 10,800 feet. As one of the most popular lakes in Texas, it is perfect for a variety of water activities and an outdoor lifestyle!\r\n\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/HighlandLakes.GIF" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Map"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Map</h3>\r\n<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27482.33310246459!2d-98.37808235!3d30.569311599999992!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x865b03c890b85f27%3A0x66ddc396f46f2257!2sLake+Lyndon+B+Johnson%2C+Texas%2C+USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1426165477704" width="600" height="450"></iframe>[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last][/five_twelfths_last][/tab]\r\n[tab title="Driving Directions"][seven_twelfths]\r\n<h3>Driving Directions</h3>\r\n<b>From Austin:</b> Approx. 55 miles / 1.10 hour by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on TX-71 W</li>\r\n	<li>Drive approx. 55 miles</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right onto FM 2147 E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>From Dallas:</b> Approx. 210 miles / 3.75 hours by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on I-35 E S</li>\r\n	<li>Get on US-67 S and take it 86 miles to TX-220 S in Erath County</li>\r\n	<li>Take a slight left onto TX-220 S</li>\r\n	<li>Follow US-281 S for 103 miles to FM 2147 W in Marble Falls</li>\r\n	<li>Continue on FM 2147 W</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>From San Antonio:</b> Approx. 98 miles / 2 hours by car\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get on I-37 N</li>\r\n	<li>Get on US-281 N and take it 90 miles to TX-71 W</li>\r\n	<li>Get on TX-71 W to FM 2147 E</li>\r\n	<li>Turn right onto FM 2147 E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/seven_twelfths][five_twelfths_last]<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d27482.33310246459!2d-98.37808235!3d30.569311599999992!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x865b03c890b85f27%3A0x66ddc396f46f2257!2sLake+Lyndon+B+Johnson%2C+Texas%2C+USA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2s!4v1426165477704" width="360" height="448"></iframe>[/five_twelfths_last][/tab][tab title="Local Weather"]\r\n<h3>Local Weather</h3>\r\nBelow is a monthly overview of the weather in the area based on data from Kingsland, Texas.\r\n\r\n[five_twelfths_last]<img class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Weather.png" alt="" />[/five_twelfths_last][button url="http://www.weather.com/weather/today/l/30.56,-98.35?lat=30.56&amp;lon=-98.35&amp;locale=en_US&amp;temp=f" size="medium" target="_blanck"]Current Weather[/button][/tab][/tabs]', 'THE AREA', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '489-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 15:30:05', '2015-03-31 15:30:05', '', 489, '489-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
